# COMPREHENSIVE DOCUMENTATION STANDARDS

**Validation**: "Rule 510 Documentation Standards Active"

## Documentation Structure Pattern Recognition

**Technical Documentation Triggers**: System architecture changes, process workflows, API modifications
**Structure Signature**:

```markdown
# Title → ## Overview → ## Prerequisites → ## Implementation → ## Examples → ## Troubleshooting → ## References
```

**Code Documentation Patterns**:

- Function docstrings with Args/Returns/Raises
- Class documentation with purpose/attributes
- Module-level documentation with usage examples
- API documentation with request/response examples

## Mermaid Diagram Requirements

**Mandatory Diagram Triggers**:

- System architecture → `graph TD` with component relationships
- Process flows → `flowchart LR` with workflow steps
- Database schemas → `erDiagram` with relationships
- Interaction flows → `sequenceDiagram` with timing

**High-Contrast, Accessible Color Scheme (Universal Standard)**:

- All diagrams (in documentation and chat) must use:
    - Black background
    - Shapes with light fill color
    - White connector lines between shapes
    - Black text for any content inside shapes
- This requirement overrides any previous color-coding guidance (e.g., phase/operation/decision colors).
- This ensures maximum accessibility and visibility for all users.

**Example:**

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["User Input"] --> B["Validation"]
    B --> C["Processing"]

    %% Set black background
    %% (Note: Some renderers require CSS or theme settings for background)
    style A fill:#f8f9fa,stroke:#ffffff,stroke-width:3px,color:#000000
    style B fill:#e9ecef,stroke:#ffffff,stroke-width:3px,color:#000000
    style C fill:#dee2e6,stroke:#ffffff,stroke-width:3px,color:#000000
    %% White connectors are default, but explicitly set if supported
```

**Accessibility Requirements**: High contrast only, clear labels, logical flow direction, consistent styling

